            <div>
                <entry xml:id="L3b53370918e34d0fb4bc332b4b903efa" n="12553">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዐደል</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain">
                        <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>ʿadal</quote>
                        </cit>
                        <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="nomen proprium">n. pr.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> (place name) the region and petty state of ʿAdāl which was
                        located around the town of Harar <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይንግሥ፡ ሥላሴ፡ በኵለሄ፡
                            በመዋዕሊሁ፡ ለዘርአ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ በዐደል፡ ወበዳለክ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                            <quote>“Regni la Trinità dappertutto durante i giorni di Zärʾa Yaʿǝqob,
                                nell’Adäl e nel Daläk!”</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2009TawaldaMadehnVittore"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 154 (234) l. 13-14 (ed.); 155 (235) l. 15-16
                                (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl> (‘Adäl è la forma gǝʾǝz per Adal, territorio musulmano vicino a
                        Harär, all’epoca, parte del sultanato dell’Ifat.’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Tedros2009TawaldaMadehnVittore"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 155 (235) n. 9</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) <nd/>
                    </sense>
                </entry>
